ConcurrentModificationException is thrown when you try to modify a collection (like a list) while iterating over it. To fix this I would syncronize ModuleManager.modules.


    synchronized (ModuleManager.modules) {
        Collections.sort(ModuleManager.modules, new ModuleComparator());
    }
or:

    List&lt;BaseModule&gt; modulesCopy;

    synchronized (ModuleManager.modules) {
        modulesCopy = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;(ModuleManager.modules);
    }

    Collections.sort(modulesCopy, new ModuleComparator());

    synchronized (ModuleManager.modules) {
        ModuleManager.modules.clear();
        ModuleManager.modules.addAll(modulesCopy);
    }

Both your if statements are the same btw

